@startuml
' @id(SEQ-TRACE-REVIEW)
' @ref(USE-TRACE-PARITY)
' @desc(SEQ-TRACE-REVIEW, "Implemented as Project::review_traceability (crates/mdd-core/src/lib.rs), called by Project::review after ID + security parity. FORWARD: for each registry @id on the current side whose prefix is in IMPLEMENTABLE_PREFIXES, every matching trace source_link is checked with resolve_source_link (file exists; .rs symbol found by traceability::extract_symbols); failures become forward_errors. REVERSE: traceability::changed_code(root, base) returns symbols + glue changed since base; an uncovered behaviour-bearing symbol (is_behaviour_kind) -> reverse_bucket_b (error), other uncovered changes -> reverse_bucket_a (warn). matched = forward_errors.is_empty() && reverse_bucket_b.is_empty(); the review gate honors traceability.parity_check.")
' Current-side sequence for review pass 3 (cycle 0013), as built.
title Traceability review — pass 3 (current)

participant "Project::review()" as Review
participant "trace.yml\nsource_links" as Trace
participant "traceability::\nchanged_code" as Engine
participant "git" as Git
participant "traceability::\nextract_symbols (syn)" as Syn
participant "TraceabilityReport" as Rep

== Forward (whole gated model) ==
loop each current-side @id with an IMPLEMENTABLE_PREFIX
  Review -> Trace : source_links for @id
  Trace --> Review : (path, symbol)*
  loop each link
    Review -> Syn : resolve_source_link (symbol in path?)
    alt resolves
      Syn --> Review : ok
    else missing
      Review -> Rep : forward_errors.push(model_id, path, symbol)
    end
  end
end

== Reverse (changeset since base) ==
Review -> Engine : changed_code(root, base)
Engine -> Git : diff --unified=0 base..worktree
Git --> Engine : hunks (file, line ranges)
Engine -> Syn : symbols overlapping hunks
Syn --> Engine : enclosing symbols + glue
Engine --> Review : ChangedCode { symbols, glue }
loop each changed symbol with no source_link
  alt is_behaviour_kind
    Review -> Rep : reverse_bucket_b.push (error)
  else glue / const / variant
    Review -> Rep : reverse_bucket_a.insert (warn)
  end
end
Rep --> Review : matched = forward empty AND bucket_b empty
@enduml
